tions division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 34.15606, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn93066937", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd"], "subject": ["augusta", "newspapers", "french-canadians", "augusta (me.)", "waterville (me.)", "waterville", "maine", "kennebec", "united states", "french"], "timestamp": "2026-07-22T08:00:47.234Z", "title": "La revue", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn93066937/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271101/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["methodist episcopal church, south"], "date": "1837", "dates": ["[1837 TO 1948]"], "description": ["Weekly Print began with vol. I, number 1 (June 24, 1837); ceased with volume 112, number 46 (November 18, 1948). \"Began as a newspaper but gradually developed a periodical format\"--Moore, South Carolina newspapers, page 210. Published: Charleston, South Carolina, 1837-1862 and 1878-1886; Augusta, Georgia, 1862-1865; Macon, Georgia, 1866-1878; Columbia, South Carolina, 1887-1894, 1899-1900 and 1919-1948; Greenville, South Carolina, 1895-1898 and 1912-1914; Orangeburg, South Carolina, 1901-1902; Spartanburg, South Carolina, 1903-1912; and Anderson, South Carolina, 1915-1918. Volumes for 1866- numbered continuously as whole no. 1465- . Issue of <Dec. 18, 1862> called also: <New ser., v. 1, no. 30> Issues for <Mar. 23, 1865> lack volume numbering. Publication suspended Apr. 20-June 22, 1865 and July 6-Aug. 24, 1865. Published for: Methodist Episcopal Church, 1837-<June 6, 1845>; for the Methodist Episcopal Church, South, <June 12, 1846>-1899; for the South Carolina Conference of the Methodist Episcopal Church, South, 1900. Mirror of the times (Macon, Ga.) may have been intended to appear also as a separately titled section of this publication. Vol. VII, No. 1, Whole Number 313 (June 16, 1843); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 24, 2024). Vol. 67, No. 28 (December 31, 1903) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 24, 2024). South Carolina Methodist advocate"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:38:15Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2024271101/", "image_url": [], "index": 10, "language": ["english"], "location": ["augusta", "southern states", "georgia", "richland", "spartanburg", "bibb", "richmond", "columbia", "greenville", "macon", "orangeburg", "charleston", "south carolina", "anderson", "united states"], "number": ["2026-04-13t21:30:13", "1431124435", "online resource", "2024271101", "2997-5689"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["May sometimes be called: Southern advocate"], "partof": ["southern christian advocate (charleston, s.c.) 1837-1948 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 16.916021, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD BX8201 .S6", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["greenville", "periodicals", "methodist episcopal church, south", "augusta", "georgia", "spartanburg", "bibb", "south carolina", "methodists", "richland", "columbia", "macon", "southern states", "newspapers", "richmond", "orangeburg", "charleston", "anderson", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:13:38.179Z", "title": "Southern Christian advocate", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2024271101/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2011254047/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1889", "dates": ["[1889 TO 1904]"], "description": ["Weekly Print began in 1889; ceased in 1904. Description based on: Vol. 11, no. 26 (Jan. 27, 1900); title from PDF masthead (Readex America's Historical Newspapers Web site, viewed Apr. 27, 2011). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 11, no. 26 (Jan. 27, 1900) (viewed Apr. 27, 2011)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:14.323Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "u