tance chart, statistics, and illustrations. Insets: Augusta -- Belgrade Mills -- Branch Mills -- China Village -- City of Hallowell -- Clinton Village -- East Vassalboro -- Farmingdale -- Fayette Mills -- Gardiner -- Getchell or Vassalboro Corner -- Litchfield Corner -- Manchester Forks -- Monmouth Village -- Mount Vernon Village -- North Monmouth -- North Vassalboro -- North Wayne -- Pittston -- Readfield Corner -- South China -- Vienna Village -- Waterville -- Wayne Village -- Weeks Mills China -- West Waterville -- Winslow Village -- Winthrop Village. LC copy sectioned in six and mounted on two pieces of cloth. LC Land ownership maps, 269 Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:39:19.315Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-04", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-04"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2012592366/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd373/g3733/g3733k/la000269.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd373/g3733/g3733k/la000269.gif#h=150&w=153", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd373:g3733:g3733k:la000269/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=2047&w=2088", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd373:g3733:g3733k:la000269/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=4094&w=4176"], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["kennebec county", "united states", "maine"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["2013-06-06t10:32:20", "2012592366", "2025-06-07t05:14:57.900000", "sheet"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["county landownership maps", "catalog", "geography and map division", "cultural landscapes"], "score": 34.3136, "shelf_id": "G3733.K4 1856 .S6", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["maps", "landowners", "cadastral maps", "united states", "kennebec county", "maine", "kennebec county (me.)"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T16:06:16.839Z", "title": "Map of Kennebec Co., Maine", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2012592366/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/81690041", "http://www.loc.gov/item/81690041/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/af0908f8-c267-5737-a4d7-2b44cba83bae", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g3733k.ct005596", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/g3733k.ct005596/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["united states. soil conservation service", "geological survey, (u.s.)"], "date": "1978", "dates": ["1978"], "description": ["Title in lower margin: Kennebec Co., Me. : N4406--W6921.5/38x47, 1978. \"Compiled in 1978 from USGS 1:24,000 and 1:62,500-scale topographic maps dated 1956-1970.\" \"Planimetry revised from aerial photographs taken 1976-1977 and other source data.\" \"1-13507.\" Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:40:52.734Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-13", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-13"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/81690041/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd373/g3733/g3733k/ct005596.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd373/g3733/g3733k/ct005596.gif#h=150&w=123", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd373:g3733:g3733k:ct005596/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1124&w=921", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd373:g3733:g3733k:ct005596/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=2249&w=1843"], "index": 9, "language": ["english"], "location": ["kennebec county", "united states", "maine"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["2025-06-07t18:34:00.300000", "2015-07-13t09:23:02", "81690041", "sheet"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["catalog", "geography and map division", "general maps"], "score": 34.3136, "shelf_id": "G3733.K4 1978 .U5", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["maps", "kennebec county (me.)", "kennebec county", "maine", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T16:20:02.142Z", "title": "Kennebec County, Maine", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/81690041/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2007626387", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2007626387/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/d34d85ff-c636-5af4-b2fd-7878ad70d08a", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g3734a.pm020170", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/g3734a.pm020170/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["ruger, a.", "beck & pauli", "stoner, j. j."], "date": "1878", "dates": ["1878"], "description": ["\"This panoramic map shows Augusta, Maine, as it appeared in 1878. Augusta has been the capital of Maine since 1827; the city is bisected by the Kennebec River. Steamboats and large sailing vessels are seen traveling on the river. An arrow drawn in the river indicates the flow of the water. On the far shore, a train runs along the Maine Central Railroad line. Further upstream, a railroad bridge and a covered bridge for pedestrians and horse-drawn carriages cross the water, connecting the two sides of the city. The Edwards Dam (built in 1837 and demolished in 1999) is also upstream. An index at the bottom of the map indicates various points of interest, including the state capitol building, court house, schools, jail, U.S. arsenal, cemetery, churches, railroad depot, railroad roundhouse and machine shop, and industry such as the gas works, tool works, cotton mill, machine shop, several saw mills, and numerous factories. Much of the industry for the city is located along the Kennebec River. The panoramic map was a cartographic form popularly used to depict U.S. and Canadian cities and towns in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. Also known as bird's-eye views or perspective maps, these maps are representations of cities portrayed as if viewed from above at an oblique angle. Not generally drawn to scale, they show street patterns, individual buildings, and major landscape features in perspective. This map is by Albert Ruger (1829-99), the first American to achieve success as a panoramic artist. Born in Prussia, Ruger immigrated to the United States and worked initially as a mason. While serving with the Ohio Volunteers during the Civil War, he drew views of Union campsites. After the war, Ruger settled in Battle Creek, Michigan, where he began his panoramic mapping career by sketching Michigan cities. In the late 1860s, Ruger formed a partnership with J.J. Stoner of Madison, Wisconsin, and together they published numerous city panoramas.\" World Digital Library."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:39:47.988Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-09", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-09"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2007626387/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd373/g3734/g3734a/pm020170.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd373/g3734/g3734a/pm020170.gif#h=150&w=225", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd373:g3734:g3734a:pm020170/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=753&w=1129", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd373:g3734:g3734a:pm020170/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=1507&w=2258"], "index": 10, "language": ["english"], "location": ["augusta", "united states", "maine"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["2022-07-14t10:49:52", "2007626387", "2025-06-07t02:18:29.300000"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["map"], "partof": ["world digital library", "panoramic maps", "catalog", "cities and towns", "geography and map division"], "score": 30.931564, "shelf_id": "G3734.A9A3 1878 .R8", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["augusta", "augusta (me.)", "aerial views", "maine", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:52:34.936Z", "title": "Bird's eye view of the city of Augusta, Maine, 1878", "type": ["cartographic"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2007626387/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2008624046", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2008624046/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/00ca00cc-1226-5795-a52a-e61e80d47167", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g3734a.la002016", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/g3734a.la002016/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["simonson, p.", "walling, henry francis", "gillet, a. g."], "date": "1851", "dates": ["1851"], "description": ["General wall maps showing selected buildings and householders' names and election districts. Also shows some lots and lot numbers on map of downtown Augusta. Relief shown by hachures on map of downtown Augusta. Oriented with north toward the upper right on map of downtown Augusta. Originally printed on 2 sheets. Includes ill. Copy imperfect: Brittle, varnished, torn, creased, stained, backed by cloth. Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image. Acquisitions control no.: 2003-38"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-04-29T15:39:18.487Z", "group": ["gmd.mar", "catalog-split-00", "catalog", "general-maps", "main-catalog-split-00"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2008624046/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd373/g3734/g3734a/la002016.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/gmd/gmd373/g3734/g3734a/la002016.gif#h=170&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd373:g3734:g3734a:la002016/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1353&w=1195", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:gmd:gmd373:g3734:g3734a:la002016/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=2706&w=2390"], "index": 11, "language": ["english"], "location": ["augusta", "united states", "maine"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["2008-12-04t13:03:23", "2008624046", "